  • Package org.cripac.isee.pedestrian.tracking

    • Class org.cripac.isee.pedestrian.tracking.Tracklet extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -6133927313545472821L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          Tracklet.Identifier id
          The identifier of the track.

        • numTracklets

          int numTracklets
          The total number of tracklets in the video. This field can be left as -1, meaning that this information is not available yet, but setting this field can help checking whether all tracklets have been obtained or processed in latter steps. So it is highly recommended that track generators should also fill in this field.

        • startFrameIndex

          int startFrameIndex
          The starting frame index of this track in the source video. User can use this to calculate the starting time of this track using the FPS information of the video. Its default value is -1, meaning the index has not been determined yet.

        • locationSequence

          Tracklet.BoundingBox[] locationSequence
          A sequence of locations (as a form of BoundingBox) of the pedestrian at each moment in the tracklet.

    • Class org.cripac.isee.pedestrian.tracking.Tracklet.BoundingBox extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -5261437055893590056L

      • Serialized Fields

        • x

          int x
          x-coordinate of the point on the left-upper corner of the bounding box.

        • y

          int y
          y-coordinate of the point on the left-upper corner of the bounding box.

        • width

          int width
          The width of the bounding box.

        • height

          int height
          The height of the bounding box.

        • patchData

          byte[] patchData
          The RGB data of the patch croped by the bounding box. If it is not availble, it should be set to null. Otherwise, it should follow the format of the 'data' field of OpenCV 2.x's Mat class. When reconstructing a OpenCV's Mat with this bounding box, first allocate a Mat with width and height same to this bounding box and format as CV_8UC3, then directly copy data of the 'patchData' field here to the 'data' field of it using functions like memcpy.

    • Class org.cripac.isee.pedestrian.tracking.Tracklet.Identifier extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -4575631684877590629L

      • Serialized Fields

        • videoID

          java.lang.String videoID
          Identifier of the video where the track is generated. This can be the storing URL of the video, or a combination of the WEBCAM_LOGIN_PARAM address real-time camera and the starting time of the video fragment.

        • serialNumber

          int serialNumber
          The serial number of the track in the video. The number is usually organized in a chronological order. Tracklet generators, like pedestrian tracking modules, should be responsible of generating this IDRANK. Its default value is -1, meaning the IDRANK has not been generated yet.
